A PAM module for the session stack to limit execution of further modules to
the first open_session for a user, or the last close_session for a user.

Returns PAM_SUCCESS for the first open_session for a user, or for the last
close_session for a user. Otherwise returns PAM_IGNORE.

Example usage to only display motd on first login:
 session	[success=ok ignore=1]	pam_once.so
 session	optional				pam_motd.so motd=/etc/motd

Contact:
 Robin McCorkell <rmccorkell@karoshi.org.uk>

See INSTALL for instructions on how to install this program. For preparing a
release, run ./autogen.sh to generate the required files.

All source files are contained in the src directory. Additional macros used in
configure.ac are stored in the m4 directory.
